The reapplied version in bd40d1de9c9ee65ef1264a36cee002f92c8d689b triggers asserts when compiling ffmpeg for x86/x86_64, if debug info is enabled:
```c
int a;
int b();
enum { c } d(char *e, int g) {
  char *f;
  do
    if (b())
      *e++ = *f++;
    else
      e++;
  while (a);
  while (g--)
    *e++ = *f++;
}
```
```console
$ clang -target x86_64-linux-gnu -c repro.c -O2 -g
clang: ../lib/Transforms/Scalar/LoopStrengthReduce.cpp:6490: bool {anonymous}::SCEVDbgValueBuilder::pushSCEV(const llvm::SCEV*): Assertion `(isa<SCEVZeroExtendExpr>(Cast) || isa<SCEVTruncateExpr>(Cast) || isa<SCEVPtrToIntExpr>(Cast) || isa<SCEVSignExtendExpr>(Cast)) && "Unexpected cast type in SCEV."' failed.
```
